"the reason is that `sqrtqmuA_v == 0` and in qtilde=True we devide over `sqrtqmuA_v`\n\nchanging the `clip` calls to clip **just** above 0 \r\n\r\n```\r\nqmu_v = tensorlib.clip(qmu(poi_test, data, pdf, init_pars, par_bounds), 1e-20, max=None)\r\nqmuA_v = tensorlib.clip(qmu(poi_test, asimov_data, pdf, init_pars, par_bounds), 1e-20, max=None)\r\n```\r\n\r\nfixes the issue\n\nAdding a note given API changes:\r\n\r\n```python\r\n>>> import pyhf\r\n>>> print(pyhf.__version__)\r\n0.4.2\r\n>>> model = pyhf.simplemodels.hepdata_like([0.005], [28.0], [5.0])\r\n>>> pyhf.infer.hypotest(1.0, [28.0] + model.config.auxdata, model, qtilde=True, return_expected=True)\r\n(array([nan]), array([1.]))\r\n>>> pyhf.infer.hypotest(1.0, [28.0] + model.config.auxdata, model, return_expected=True)\r\n(array([1.]), array([1.]))\r\n```\n\n```python\r\n>>> print(pyhf.__version__)\r\n0.5.0\r\n>>> model = pyhf.simplemodels.hepdata_like([0.005], [28.0], [5.0])\r\n>>> pyhf.infer.hypotest(1.0, [28.0] + model.config.auxdata, model, qtilde=True, return_expected=True)\r\n/Users/kratsg/.virtualenvs/pyhf/lib/python3.7/site-packages/pyhf/infer/calculators.py:165: RuntimeWarning: invalid value encountered in double_scalars\r\n  teststat = (qmu - qmu_A) / (2 * self.sqrtqmuA_v)\r\n(array([nan]), array([1.]))\r\n>>> pyhf.infer.hypotest(1.0, [28.0] + model.config.auxdata, model, return_expected=True)\r\n(array([1.]), array([1.]))\r\n```\r\n\r\njust noting that this is still a thing."